OL,4,CMan' pleads guilty to fly-tipping
OL,6,FMr. Williams, of Bell Street in
OL,7,FTrecynon, was then requested to
OL,8,Fproduce transfer notes for the waste
OL,9,Fhe had disposed of around the time of
OL,10,Fthe offence, which he did not do.
OL,12,FWith the substantial evidence against
OL,13,Fhim, he was referred to the courts for
OL,14,Fillegal waste disposal under Section
OL,15,F33 of the Environmental Protection Act
OL,16,F1990, which defines the offence of fly-
OL,17,Ftipping as the "prohibition on
OL,18,Funauthorised or harmful deposit,
OL,19,Ftreatment or disposal etc. of waste".
OL,20,FSuch violators risk facing significant
OL,21,Ffines.
