OL,3,CBusinessman known as the 'Recycling
OL,4,CMan' pleads guilty to fly-tipping
OL,6,FMr Williams appeared in court on
OL,7,FWednesday, 7 August, where he pleaded
OL,8,Fguilty to fly-tipping. He was handed a
OL,9,F12-month community order, which
OL,10,Fincluded 100 hours of unpaid work, and
OL,11,Fwas ordered to pay costs of #1,001.51
OL,12,Fand a victim surcharge of #114, which
OL,13,Fcame at a total of #1,115.51.
OL,15,FA spokesperson for Rhondda Cynon Taf
OL,16,FCouncil said: "Fly-tipping will not be
OL,17,Ftolerated, ever. There is never an
OL,18,Fexcuse to blight our towns, streets
OL,19,Fand villages with waste, and we will
OL,20,Ffind those responsible and hold them
OL,21,Fto account.
